<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-02-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-02-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="479" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d479">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Clay</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 124.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-02-07"><hi rend="italic">February</hi> 7, 1865.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 8th ultimo, No. 68,
                            treating of the emancipation of the serfs, and the promulgation by the
                            Emperor of a new code of laws, has <pb facs="0443" n="369" xml:id="pg_369"/> been received. These reforms are very creditable
                            to the government of Russia, and they cannot but be gratifying to
                            friends of liberty and humanity throughout the world.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Cassius M. Clay,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>